news.title: Mishandling of construction waste in Bengaluru creating many problems, say experts
news.para: According to the C&D waste management Rule 2016 and BBMP, the waste generators are supposed to dispose of their waste at facilities in Chikkajala and Kannur by furnishing a copy of the approved C&D waste management plan and by paying a notified service charge of Rs 134 per metric tonne.

news.title: Government inviting investments to develop urban sector: Kerala CM
news.para: The Greater Cochin Development Authority (GCDA) is organizing the event in association with the Association of Municipalities and Development Authorities (AMDA).

news.title: Rs 80 crore house tax evasion detected in Lucknow in three years
news.para: The survey revealed that owners of around 3.26 lakh new houses, constructed in the past two years, have not registered themselves for property tax.

news.title: Grade A offices of about 120 million sq ft can be refurbished in top six cities: Report
news.para: Real estate due diligence can capture a slice of the 300 million sq ft pie of existing and upcoming commercial office buildings.

news.title: Residential sector grows 15% across top eight cities in Q3 2022: Report
news.para: Similar robust activity was observed in new launches growing 15% year-on-year (YoY) to 69,687 units in Q3 2022. All markets saw average prices increase in the range of 3% to 10% YoY during this period.

news.title: Net absorption in office space touch 9.86 million sq ft in Q2 FY23: Report
news.para: Delhi NCR and Bengaluru are the two biggest office markets in terms of Jan-Sep 2022 gross leasing activity followed by Mumbai. These three markets account for over two-thirds share of occupier activity in the first nine months of the 2022 calendar year.

news.title: Livspace earmarks $100 million for strategic acquisitions
news.para: The company is fuelling a significant part of this corpus through its recent $180 million fundraise led by private equity major KKR, announced in February this year. The funding valued the company at $1.2 billion.

news.title: Qualcomm leases over 1.8 million sq ft space in K Raheja's Hyderabad IT park
news.para: The company's offices in Hyderabad are likely to be part of this consolidation plan. The new office is expected to accommodate over 17,000 employees, including its existing staff in Hyderabad that is expected to shift here and new joinees.

news.title: PE investment in real estate up 40% in Apr-Sep to $2.8 billion: Report
news.para: As per the report, investments by foreign investors contributed around 78 per cent to the total inflow in the first half of this fiscal, reflecting their strong confidence in Indian real estate.

news.title: Life in a 95-sq-foot apartment! How tinier living spaces are taking over Tokyo
news.para: With its high property prices and the world's most populous metropolitan area, Tokyo has long been known for small accommodations.

news.title: Gujarat: Sale deeds pile up at registration offices
news.para: This backlog arose because of a clarification that the state government had issued three months ago on the procedures to be followed for collection of stamp duty in case the property belonged to an old co-operative housing society.

news.title: Kolkata civic body departments team up to bring new properties under tax net
news.para: This tie-up will fetch the civic body substantial revenue by bringing the new constructions under the property tax net.

news.title: PAP moves Bombay HC, challenges land regularisation in Cidco area
news.para: The GR was issued on February 25, 2022, to regularize the mass scale illegal houses by allowing 30% discount in Cidco’s reserved price for plots up to 200 sq metres and 60% for 201 sq metres to 500 sq metres area.

news.title: Telangana to auction 19 properties in 10 districts
news.para: ​Apart from properties in and around Hyderabad which would be e-auctioned, the others across the state will be done via physicial bidding process.

news.title: Ambuja Cements gets shareholders' nod for raising Rs 20,000 crore from Adani group firm
news.para: Resolutions to appoint Adani Group Chairman Gautam Adani, his son Karan Adani and two directors and four independent directors on the board of Ambuja Cements were also approved by the shareholders.
